<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Your Clinical Education Journey</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Nunito:wght@400;500;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  body { font-family: 'Nunito', sans-serif; background: #f9f9f9; padding: 24px; color: #222222; }
  .page { max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .banner { width: 100%; border-radius: 14px; display: block; margin-bottom: 1.75rem; }

  /* OBJECTIVE */
  .objective-card { background: #ffffff; border: 1px solid #e0e0e0; border-left: 5px solid #c48b2b; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.4rem 1.6rem; margin-bottom: 1.75rem; }
  .card-label { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 800; color: #c48b2b; letter-spacing: 0.09em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .objective-text { font-size: 17px; color: #222222; line-height: 1.7; }

  /* INTRO */
  .intro-text { font-size: 17px; color: #333333; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1.75rem; }

  /* SECTION LABEL */
  .section-label { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 800; color: #666666; letter-spacing: 0.09em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 0.85rem; }

  /* TIMELINE */
  .timeline { margin-bottom: 1.75rem; }
  .semester-block { background: #ffffff; border: 1px solid #e0e0e0; border-radius: 12px; margin-bottom: 12px; overflow: hidden; cursor: pointer; transition: box-shadow 0.2s; }
  .semester-block:hover { box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(41,91,48,0.12); }
  .semester-header { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 14px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem; background: #ffffff; }
  .semester-badge { background: #295b30; color: #ffffff; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 800; border-radius: 8px; padding: 4px 12px; white-space: nowrap; letter-spacing: 0.04em; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .semester-title { font-size: 17px; font-weight: 700; color: #222222; flex: 1; }
  .semester-meta { font-size: 13px; color: #666666; margin-left: auto; white-space: nowrap; }
  .chevron { font-size: 18px; color: #295b30; transition: transform 0.25s; margin-left: 10px; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .chevron.open { transform: rotate(180deg); }
  .semester-body { display: none; border-top: 1px solid #eeeeee; padding: 1.1rem 1.25rem 1.25rem; background: #f9fdf9; }
  .semester-body.open { display: block; }
  .exp-row { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .exp-row:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .exp-icon { width: 36px; height: 36px; border-radius: 8px; background: #295b30; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 18px; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px; }
  .exp-content {}
  .exp-title { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; color: #295b30; margin-bottom: 3px; }
  .exp-desc { font-size: 15px; color: #444444; line-height: 1.6; }
  .ocr-tag { display: inline-block; background: #c48b2b; color: #ffffff; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; border-radius: 6px; padding: 2px 9px; margin-left: 8px; vertical-align: middle; letter-spacing: 0.04em; }

  /* HOURS SECTION */
  .hours-card { background: #295b30; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem 1.6rem; margin-bottom: 1.75rem; }
  .hours-title { font-size: 19px; font-weight: 800; color: #ffffff; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .hours-sub { font-size: 16px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .hours-highlight { display: inline-block; background: #c48b2b; color: #ffffff; font-size: 36px; font-weight: 800; border-radius: 10px; padding: 0.4rem 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .hours-bullets { list-style: none; }
  .hours-bullets li { font-size: 16px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6; padding: 0.3rem 0; padding-left: 1.4rem; position: relative; }
  .hours-bullets li::before { content: "✓"; position: absolute; left: 0; color: #c48b2b; font-weight: 800; }

  /* ASHA CALLOUT */
  .asha-card { background: #ffffff; border: 1px solid #e0e0e0; border-left: 5px solid #295b30; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.4rem 1.6rem; margin-bottom: 1.75rem; }
  .asha-title { font-size: 17px; font-weight: 800; color: #295b30; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .asha-text { font-size: 16px; color: #333333; line-height: 1.75; }

  /* REMINDER CALLOUT */
  .reminder-card { background: #fff8ec; border: 1px solid #c48b2b; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.3rem 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.75rem; display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: flex-start; }
  .reminder-icon { font-size: 26px; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px; }
  .reminder-title { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; color: #c48b2b; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .reminder-text { font-size: 15px; color: #444444; line-height: 1.65; }

  /* CONTACT */
  .contact-card { background: #295b30; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.3rem 1.6rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; }
  .contact-title { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; color: #ffffff; margin-bottom: 3px; }
  .contact-detail { font-size: 14px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85); }
  .contact-detail a { color: #c48b2b; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="page">

  <!-- BANNER: replace src with your Canvas image URL -->
  <img src="clinical_journey_banner.png" alt="Your Clinical Education Journey" class="banner" />

  <!-- LEARNING OBJECTIVE -->
  <div class="objective-card">
    <div class="card-label">🎯 Learning Objective</div>
    <div class="objective-text">By the end of this page, you will be able to describe the sequence of clinical experiences in the OBU MS-SLP program, understand how your clinical hours accumulate toward the 375-hour requirement, and explain how those hours connect to ASHA certification.</div>
  </div>

  <!-- INTRO -->
  <p class="intro-text">Your clinical education doesn't happen all at once — it unfolds intentionally across four semesters, each building on the last. You'll move from simulated clinical experiences in your first semester to real-world externships in educational, medical, and advanced clinical settings. Every experience is designed to grow your confidence and competence, step by step. Click on each semester below to explore what happens when.</p>

  <!-- TIMELINE -->
  <div class="section-label">Your clinical education sequence — fall cohort</div>
  <div class="timeline">

    <!-- Semester 1 -->
    <div class="semester-block" onclick="toggleSemester('s1')">
      <div class="semester-header">
        <div class="semester-badge">Semester 1</div>
        <div class="semester-title">Fall &nbsp;·&nbsp; Building Your Foundation</div>
        <div class="chevron" id="chevron-s1">&#8964;</div>
      </div>
      <div class="semester-body" id="s1">
        <div class="exp-row">
          <div class="exp-icon">🏫</div>
          <div class="exp-content">
            <div class="exp-title">On-Campus Residency: Education/Pediatric <span class="ocr-tag">OCR 1</span></div>
            <div class="exp-desc">Your first immersive clinical experience happens right here on the OBU campus during Semester 1. Over five intensive days, you'll follow a single pediatric client case from referral through IEP development, practicing real clinical skills in a supported environment alongside your cohort and faculty.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="exp-row">
          <div class="exp-icon">💻</div>
          <div class="exp-content">
            <div class="exp-title">Virtual Practicum (SLP 5212)</div>
            <div class="exp-desc">Running alongside your coursework for the full semester, the Virtual Practicum uses Simucase — a clinical simulation platform — to give you supervised clinical hours before you enter an external placement. Hours completed here count toward your 375-hour requirement.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Semester 2 -->
    <div class="semester-block" onclick="toggleSemester('s2')">
      <div class="semester-header">
        <div class="semester-badge">Semester 2</div>
        <div class="semester-title">Spring &nbsp;·&nbsp; Entering the School Setting</div>
        <div class="chevron" id="chevron-s2">&#8964;</div>
      </div>
      <div class="semester-body" id="s2">
        <div class="exp-row">
          <div class="exp-icon">🎒</div>
          <div class="exp-content">
            <div class="exp-title">Education/Pediatric Externship (SLP 6002)</div>
            <div class="exp-desc">Your first real-world externship places you in an educational setting — typically a school — where you'll work with children under the supervision of a qualified SLP clinical educator. You'll apply the skills you practiced in Semester 1 with real clients, real data, and real IEPs. This placement runs for the full semester, a minimum of three days per week.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Semester 3 -->
    <div class="semester-block" onclick="toggleSemester('s3')">
      <div class="semester-header">
        <div class="semester-badge">Semester 3</div>
        <div class="semester-title">Summer &nbsp;·&nbsp; Expanding Your Clinical Scope</div>
        <div class="chevron" id="chevron-s3">&#8964;</div>
      </div>
      <div class="semester-body" id="s3">
        <div class="exp-row">
          <div class="exp-icon">🏥</div>
          <div class="exp-content">
            <div class="exp-title">On-Campus Residency: Medical/Adult <span class="ocr-tag">OCR 2</span></div>
            <div class="exp-desc">Your second OCR brings you back to campus for another intensive week, this time focused on adult and medical populations — dysphagia, neurogenic disorders, voice, and more. You'll work through a new case with new faculty and new peers, deepening your clinical reasoning across a different scope of practice.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="exp-row">
          <div class="exp-icon">🩺</div>
          <div class="exp-content">
            <div class="exp-title">Medical/Adult Externship (SLP 6212)</div>
            <div class="exp-desc">This externship places you in a medical or clinical setting — hospitals, rehabilitation centers, outpatient clinics, or skilled nursing facilities — where you'll work with adult populations under clinical supervision. Like your education externship, this runs for the full semester at a minimum of three days per week.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Semester 4 -->
    <div class="semester-block" onclick="toggleSemester('s4')">
      <div class="semester-header">
        <div class="semester-badge">Semester 4</div>
        <div class="semester-title">Fall &nbsp;·&nbsp; Advanced Clinical Practice</div>
        <div class="chevron" id="chevron-s4">&#8964;</div>
      </div>
      <div class="semester-body" id="s4">
        <div class="exp-row">
          <div class="exp-icon">⭐</div>
          <div class="exp-content">
            <div class="exp-title">Advanced Clinical Externship (SLP 6402)</div>
            <div class="exp-desc">Your final externship is an advanced placement — often a telepractice setting or a specialized clinical context — where you'll bring together everything you've learned across the program. By this point, you're functioning with greater independence and demonstrating the readiness for entry-level professional practice. This externship is the capstone of your clinical education.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <!-- HOURS SECTION -->
  <div class="section-label">The 375-hour requirement</div>
  <div class="hours-card">
    <div class="hours-title">Your clinical hour goal</div>
    <div class="hours-sub">The OBU MS-SLP program requires you to complete a minimum of:</div>
    <div class="hours-highlight">375 supervised clinical hours</div>
    <ul class="hours-bullets">
      <li>Hours are accumulated across all four clinical experiences: Virtual Practicum, Education/Pediatric Externship, Medical/Adult Externship, and Advanced Clinical Externship</li>
      <li>All hours must meet ASHA certification standards (Standard V-C) — meaning they involve direct client contact under qualified supervision</li>
      <li>If you completed supervised clinical hours as an undergraduate, up to 50 of those hours may be applied — documentation must be submitted to and approved by the Director of Clinical Education</li>
      <li>Every hour must be logged accurately and promptly in Exxat — documentation is your responsibility</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- ASHA CONNECTION -->
  <div class="asha-card">
    <div class="asha-title">Why your hours matter beyond graduation</div>
    <div class="asha-text">Your 375 clinical hours are not just a program requirement — they are a foundational piece of your path to the <strong>Certificate of Clinical Competence in Speech-Language Pathology (CCC-SLP)</strong>, the national credential awarded by ASHA. After graduation, you'll complete a Clinical Fellowship (CF) year and pass the Praxis exam to earn your CCC-SLP. Your clinical hours from this program form the verified foundation that makes you eligible for that process. Accurate, well-documented hours from Day 1 matter — they follow you into your career.</div>
  </div>

  <!-- REMINDER -->
  <div class="reminder-card">
    <div class="reminder-icon">📋</div>
    <div>
      <div class="reminder-title">Your hours live in Exxat</div>
      <div class="reminder-text">All clinical hours must be logged in Exxat — the program's clinical tracking platform. Hours that are not documented in Exxat cannot be verified or applied toward your requirement. Log your hours promptly after each clinical session and never wait until the end of a placement to catch up. See the <strong>Getting Started in Exxat</strong> page in this module for details.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- CONTACT -->
  <div class="contact-card">
    <div style="font-size:30px; color:#c48b2b; flex-shrink:0;">✉</div>
    <div>
      <div class="contact-title">Questions about your clinical sequence or hours?</div>
      <div class="contact-detail">Dr. Becky Jones, Director of Clinical Education &nbsp;·&nbsp; <a href="mailto:becky.jones@okbu.edu">becky.jones@okbu.edu</a> &nbsp;·&nbsp; 405-585-4625</div>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

<script>
  function toggleSemester(id) {
    var body = document.getElementById(id);
    var chevron = document.getElementById('chevron-' + id);
    if (body.classList.contains('open')) {
      body.classList.remove('open');
      chevron.classList.remove('open');
    } else {
      body.classList.add('open');
      chevron.classList.add('open');
    }
  }
</script>
</body>
</html>
